In the real world, ducks are omnivores, with a meat-heavy diet. They catch and eat small fish, insects, frogs if they're small enough, molluscs, and so on, as well as vegetation. If anything their dietary range is at least as wide as that of most primates in the wild. Wider, as primates can't digest grass, but ducks can. So in the real world, the beak works out pretty well for them.

Now, ducks don't have lips, which would introduce a lot of difficulties with speech, and a lot of other things. On the other hand, with lips they could make the duckface, and I don't think the world is ready for ducks making the duckface.
